1.8.0 — 2026-07-21
  - Real station-logo image model (live source + bundle re-synced; 3 sample logo
    assets added under logos/). Logos are now real image assets with arbitrary
    aspect ratios, not just monogram tiles. New ANDROID §4.5 "Station logos — real
    image assets & per-surface fit" is the authoritative guidance for MAX COVERAGE:
    the containment invariant (Fit, never crop/overflow, plate-separate-from-image),
    bounding-box crop + record-aspect on assign, and the per-surface budget below.
    - Hero: a real logo REPLACES the big call sign (logo sized to a generous share of
      the card, Fit); the call sign becomes a small label beneath it. No real logo →
      NO monogram tile on the hero (just call sign + frequency). Star always corner.
    - Preset tiles + prev/next peek cards: real logo fills a borderless transparent
      plate (Fit; landscape-tolerant so wordmarks read); freq + call sign hidden on a
      logo tile. No logo → monogram cube + (frequency then call sign).
    - Nearby search: logos REMOVED entirely (small square can't render detailed/wide
      logos legibly; low-traffic surface). Row = freq · callsign · city/genre · signal ·
      distance. §6.2 updated; dead logo paths deleted from NearbyPicker source.
  - Call signs now display as the 4 core letters only — `-FM`/`-AM` suffixes and
    hyphens stripped everywhere (e.g. WWHG-FM → WWHG). README + §4.2/§4.3/§6.2.
  - Logo-search window (§6.4) now opens on a LANDING view, not a search:
    - Has a logo → shows the current logo + two options, **Display Call Sign** and
      **Display Frequency** (both ON by default), + "Search for a different logo".
    - No logo → "No Logo Installed" + "Search for a logo".
    - The two options affect the HERO CARD ONLY, saved per station; unchecking hides
      that element on the hero when tuned. Search runs only on button press.
      New demoState value `landing` (now the default). §6.4 rewritten.
  - Settings TUNER sources corrected to the shipping set (§6.3 + README surface 4):
    RTL-SDR (USB SDR, detected/not) · NWD / NOWADA built-in (integrated head-unit FM
    tuner) · FYT / DuduOS built-in (unavailable — greyed) · Auto (probe all sources).
  - NOTE: the per-surface reference PNGs still show monogram tiles; the real-logo
    hero/preset/peek visuals are documented in §4.5 and render live from
    CarFmLive.dc.html (same live-render policy as the overlay states).

1.7.0 (2026-07-20)
  - Preset logo search implemented (new surface + live source/bundle re-synced),
    per the incoming Claude Code handoff (docs/design/handoff-logo-search.md):
    - New modal LogoSearchOverlay.dc.html: opens over the face, runs the search on
      open (no query field), header shows the station + exact query string, four
      image candidates in a 2×2 grid, tap-to-select (blue border+fill+check; never
      red/green), Confirm/Cancel, plus loading / no-results / error / saving states.
      Responsive (2×2 fits the narrow track), light/dark. demoState prop flips the
      five states for review. Backend (search/save-as-manual/tile-refresh) is host-
      side. New ANDROID §6.4 + README surface 5.
    - Preset tile trigger is now a magnifier-over-picture "logo-search" badge (was a
      pencil that fired a placeholder toast); opens the window for that station. Kept
      visually distinct from the Nearby magnifier-over-tower (§7).
  - Preset drag-reorder reworked to gap-opening (live source + bundle re-synced):
    long-press now flows straight into the drag with the same finger (continuous
    gesture; a >12dp pre-fire move cancels so the rail still scrolls). Sibling tiles
    slide apart to open a real gap at the insertion slot (wiggle frozen during drag;
    geometry locked to slot rects captured at drag start so it doesn't oscillate).
    Commits on release with the FLIP slide. Replaces the dashed drop-outline of 1.6.1.
    §4.3/§8 + README updated.

1.6.1 (2026-07-20)
  - Fixed erratic preset drag-reorder (live source + bundle copies re-synced).
    Live mid-drag reordering fought the index-keyed preset list (node/content
    swap desynced from the direct-manipulated drag transform), making cards jump.
    Reworked to commit-on-drop: the dragged tile floats freely under the pointer,
    the nearest preset shows a dashed drop outline, and the reorder commits once on
    release with a FLIP reflow (dropped tile slides from the finger into its slot).
    FLIP translate now divides by the stage scale factor. §4.3/§8 + README updated.

1.6.0 (2026-07-20)
  - Preset reorder redesigned (live source + bundle copies re-synced):
    - Drag-to-reorder replaces the on-screen ‹ › move arrows. In reorder mode a
      picked-up tile lifts (scale 1.06 + shadow, touch-action:none) and tracks the
      pointer; remaining tiles reflow live via the existing FLIP slide and the tile
      settles into the nearest slot on release. §4.3/§8 + README updated.
    - Added a per-tile logo-edit badge (blue pencil, top-left) that opens the app's
      station-logo search (deep-link; prototype shows a placeholder toast). The ✕
      remove badge and DONE button are unchanged. §4.3 + Behavior list updated.

